<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10289</anchor> <rss>erct-0029.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr>  <route>erct-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10290</anchor> <rss>erct-003R.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003R</addr>  <route>erct-003R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001E.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001E" title="The truncation hierarchy">The truncation hierarchy</link> › propositional truncation and existence</title> <parent>erct-001E</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10291</anchor> <rss>erct-0028.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0028</addr>  <route>erct-0028.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Propositional truncation</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0028.agda" type="external">erct-0028.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any type <tex>A</tex> we have a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link> <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex> equipped with a unit map <tex>\eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \colon  A  \to \mathsf {toProp} \, {A}</tex>; moreover, we have the following induction principle: for any family of <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">propositions</link> <tex>B \colon   \mathsf {toProp} \, A  \to   \mathsf {Prop}</tex>, any function <tex>b \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  B \mathopen {} \left ( \eta _{ \mathsf {prop}} \, x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> extends to a function <tex>b^ \sharp   \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x \colon \mathsf {toProp} \, A \right ) \mathclose {} } }  Bx</tex>.</p><p>When we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>, we will say that <tex>A</tex> is <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10292</anchor> <rss>erct-002A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr>  <route>erct-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10293</anchor> <rss>erct-0029.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0029</addr>  <route>erct-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Surjection</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>surjective</strong></em> when for any <tex>b \colon  B</tex>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-002A.xml" type="local" addr="erct-002A" title="Inhabitation and existence">inhabited</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10294</anchor> <rss>erct-003F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003F</addr>  <route>erct-003F.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Bijection</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003F.agda" type="external">erct-003F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>bijective</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10295</anchor> <rss>erct-002A.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-002A</addr>  <route>erct-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inhabitation and existence</title>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A type <tex>A</tex> is called <em><strong>inhabited</strong></em> when we have an element of <tex>\mathsf {toProp} \, A</tex>. When we say <em><strong>there exists</strong></em>, we refer to inhabitation.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10296</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10297</anchor> <rss>erct-003F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003F</addr>  <route>erct-003F.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>10</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Bijection</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003F.agda" type="external">erct-003F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called <em><strong>bijective</strong></em> when it is a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional map</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10298</anchor> <rss>erct-002X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr>  <route>erct-002X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10299</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002X</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10300</anchor> <rss>erct-002Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Y</addr>  <route>erct-002Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">Bijections</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Y.agda" type="external">erct-002Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link> <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10301</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002Y</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>Fixing <tex>b:B</tex>, we must check that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link>; because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0028" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> to observe that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001Q" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <em>inhabited</em> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10302</anchor> <rss>erct-002B.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002B</addr>  <route>erct-002B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Being a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjection</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002B.agda" type="external">erct-002B.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>That a given map <tex>f \colon  E \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjective</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10303</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-002B</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>By <ref addr="erct-001B" href="erct-001B.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10304</anchor> <rss>erct-000K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000K</addr>  <route>erct-000K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Full and faithful <link href="erct-000I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000I" title="Functor between precategories">functor</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000K.agda" type="external">erct-000K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <link href="erct-000I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000I" title="Functor between precategories">functor</link> <tex>F \colon  C  \to  D</tex> is called (<em><strong>full</strong></em>, <em><strong>faithful</strong></em>) when the action on arrows is valued in (<link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjections</link>, <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional maps</link>) respectively. It is common to refer to a <em>full</em> and <em>faithful</em> functor as <em><strong>fully faithful</strong></em>.</p><p>Fullness and faithfulness are both <em><link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">properties</link></em> of a functor.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10305</anchor> <rss>erct-000L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-000L</addr>  <route>erct-000L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategories</link></title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000L.agda" type="external">erct-000L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>For any <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategory</link> <tex>C</tex>, the type <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \sum _{ \mathopen {} \left ( D :  \mathsf {Precategory} \right ) \mathclose {} } } {D \cong  C}</tex> of <link href="erct-000J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000J" title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms of precategories</link> onto <tex>C</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>10306</anchor>  <taxon>Proof</taxon>    <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors>  <parent>erct-000L</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>The type of isomorphisms onto <tex>C</tex> is inhabited, considering the identity isomorphism <tex>1_{ C } \colon  C \cong  C</tex>. Therefore, it suffices to show that the type of <link href="erct-000J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000J" title="Isomorphism of precategories">isomorphisms</link> onto <tex>C</tex> depicted below is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">proposition</link>:</p>

  <tex display="block">     \begin {aligned}     D &amp;:  \mathsf {Precategory} \\      F &amp;: D \cong  C     \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>We unfold the definitions of a <link href="erct-000B.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000B" title="Precategory">precategories</link> and <link href="erct-000J.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000J" title="Isomorphism of precategories">their isomorphisms</link>, dropping <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001I" title="Proposition">propositional</link> axioms:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_0&amp;:  \mathsf {Type} \\        D_1&amp;:D_0 \to  D_0 \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_0&amp;: D_0 \to  C_0 \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \to   C \mathopen {} \left ( F_0x , F_0y \right ) \mathclose {} \\        h_1 &amp;:  \mathsf {isBiinvertible} \, F_0 \\        h_2 &amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathsf {isPropMap} \mathopen {} \left ( F_1xy \right ) \mathclose {}         \\        h_3 &amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }   \mathsf {isSurjection} \mathopen {} \left ( F_1xy \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>A function that is both <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001T" title="N-truncated map">propositional</link> and a <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0029" title="Surjection">surjection</link>, i.e. a <link href="erct-003F.xml" type="local" addr="erct-003F" title="Bijection">bijection</link>, is an <link href="erct-000V.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000V" title="Equivalence of types">equivalence</link> by <ref addr="erct-002Z" href="erct-002Z.xml" taxon="Corollary"/>. We can therefore repackage our telescope equivalently:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_0&amp;:  \mathsf {Type} \\        D_1&amp;:D_0 \to  D_0 \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_0&amp;: D_0 \cong  C_0 \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y: D_0 \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \cong   C \mathopen {} \left ( F_0x , F_0y \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>By the univalence principle for types, we may contract <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( D_0,F_0 \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> to <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( \left \lvert C \right \rvert ,  1_{ \left \lvert C \right \rvert } \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>:</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_1&amp;: \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to   \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_1&amp;:  \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y \in  C \right ) \mathclose {} } }  D_1xy \cong   C \mathopen {} \left ( x , y \right ) \mathclose {}       \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>Next we rewrite using the univalence principles for functions and families of types (<ref addr="erct-0015" href="erct-0015.xml" taxon="Axiom"/>, <ref addr="erct-001D" href="erct-001D.xml" taxon="Axiom"/>):</p>

  <tex display="block">      \begin {aligned}       D_1&amp;: \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to   \left \lvert C \right \rvert \to \mathsf {Set} \\        F_1&amp;: D_1 =  \lambda x,y \mathpunct {.} { C \mathopen {} \left ( x , y \right ) \mathclose {} }      \end {aligned}   </tex>

  <p>By the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for functions</link>, the data above is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" addr="erct-001H" title="Contractible type">contractible</link>.</p>
